  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "LORETTA KOZAK",
    "text": "And living the rest of your life with guilt that you are the one that survived while the rest of the family, most of them, were killed. Why did I survive? He would tell me so many times. Why didn't they kill me? And these are questions that I imagine goes through their minds time and time again. And for the rest of their lives, it will never really end.",
